<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
  <title>Welcome to Mama Mbelle's!</title>
  <style>
    h1
    {
      font-family: cambria;
      font-size: 48pt;
      color: #C0504D;
    }
    
    h2
    {
      font-family: cambria;
      font-size: 14pt;
      color: #C0504D;
    }
    
    p
    {
      font-family: calibri;
      font-size: 11pt;
    }
    
    td
    {
      vertical-align: top;
    }
    
    .menu 
    {
      width: 525px;
    }
    
    .gutter
    {
      width: 10px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <table>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <img src="/Content/images/mb_logo.png" alt="logo" />
      </td>
      <td>
        <div class="menu">
          <h1>
            breakfast</h1>
          <h2>
            Deep Fried Pancakes</h2>
          <p>
            Crispy on the outside, warm and gooey on the inside, these pancakes are the specialty
            of the house. Ask for chocolate chips inside!</p>
          <h2>
            Eggs</h2>
          <p>
            Eggs served over hard or over really hard.</p>
          <h2>
            Porridge</h2>
          <p>
            Lumps can be repaired; ask your server.</p>
          <h2>
            Banana Bread</h2>
          <p>
            Whole wheat chocolate chip banana bread that melts in your mouth.</p>
          <h2>
            Toast</h2>
          <p>
            Toast buttered and grape jellied or strawberry jammed. Yum!</p>
          <h2>
            Turkey Bacon or Sausage</h2>
          <p>
            No eyelashes!</p>
        </div>
      </td>
      <td><div class="gutter"></div></td>
      <td>
        <div class="menu">
          <h1>
            beverages</h1>
          <h2>
            Tea</h2>
          <p>
            Both kinds: warm Chai or lukewarm Chai.</p>
          <h2>
            Bottled Water</h2>
          <p>
            Pay no attention to the shape or size of the bottle – it’s water. Honest!</p>
        </div>
      </td>
      <td><div class="gutter"></div></td>
      <td>
        <div class="menu">
          <h1>
            lunch &amp; dinner</h1>
          <h2>
            Taco Salad</h2>
          <p>
            Turkey, lettuce, cheese and croutons with a hand-made spicy Ranch. Magnifico!</p>
          <h2>
            Tilapia</h2>
          <p>
            Lightly breaded and cooked to perfection. Bones will be removed if you ask nicely.</p>
          <h2>
            Meatloaf & Twice-Baked Potatoes</h2>
          <p>
            Another Mama Mbelle specialty, served with just enough ketchup inside.</p>
          <h2>
            Chicken Cordon Bleu</h2>
          <p>
            Hand-shaped baked chicken stuffed with ham and cheese. Gratzi!</p>
          <h2>
            Chicken Pot Pie</h2>
          <p>
            Chicken, gravy and veggies baked in a pie crust. Down home comfort food!</p>
          <h2>
            Chicken ala King</h2>
          <p>
            The newest addition to Mbelle’s menu; good if you pick out the green peppers.</p>
        </div>
      </td>
      <td><div class="gutter"></div></td>
      <td>
        <div class="menu">
          <h1>
            dessert</h1>
          <h2>
            Chocolate Chip Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            Whole wheat or oatmeal, warm and fresh from the oven and can be accompanied with
            Renaissance ice cream with your choice of flavors (if you bring it with you).</p>
          <h2>
            Boston Cream Pie</h2>
          <p>
            Now in both full and personal size. Messy but worth it!</p>
        </div>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
